**who —** NINTENDO GAME BOY — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** The Game Boy won the handheld wars with worse specs than its rivals — a monochrome screen, a CPU between the 8080 and Z80 — and unbeatable battery life, durability, and games. Tetris in the box and weeks on four AA batteries beat colour screens that died in hours.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The Game Boy won the handheld wars with worse specs than its rivals — a monochrome screen, a CPU between the 8080 and Z80 — and unbeatable battery life, durability, and games. Tetris in the box and weeks on four AA batteries beat colour screens that died in hours.

